y higher likelihood of being classified as \"High Risk\".\n2. **Interest Rates & Payment Delays**: Higher interest rates and frequent payment delays from the due date are strongly associated with higher credit risk. Minimizing the occurrence of delayed payments is a primary path to reducing risk.\n3. **Credit History Age Matters**: Longer credit history (`Credit_History_Age_Total` in months) is a strong positive indicator of lower risk. Newer credit accounts pose a higher predictive risk, pointing to the need for stricter evaluation of younger files.\n4. **Data Preprocessing & Cleaning are Vital**: Handling outliers and stripping corrupted text values (such as trailing underscores and negative balances) was essential to achieving high predictive accuracy.\n5. **No Data Leakage Guarantee**: By splitting the training data prior to imputation, scaling, and feature selection, we ensure our model performance metrics are completely realistic and generalize well to unseen test data.","metadata":{}}]}